{
  "name": "11263-mcp-env-headers-bypass",
  "target_process": "warp-oss",
  "_purpose": "Reproduction evidence for warpdotdev/warp#11263. Runs against a warp-oss binary built WITH DEMO-PATCH-B (so SECRETS_REGEX compiles when the toggle is flipped) but WITHOUT DEMO-PATCH-C (no raw-input scan in parse_templatable_json before from_user_json runs). The recipe proves: with secret redaction visibly ON, a save whose secret sits in headers.Authorization is silently accepted (BUG), while the same secret in the top-level `url` is correctly rejected by PR #10839's predicate (control). The bug is the templatize_field call on env/headers that replaces the secret with a `{{placeholder}}` before the predicate scans `template.json`.",
  "_safety": "Token is the deterministic placeholder `sk-FAKE0000000000FAKEdemoWARP11263`. Matches the Generic SK regex from custom_secret_regex_list.",
  "_state_touched": "Adds MCP entry `demo-hdr-bypass-11263` to MY MCPS during Phase C. Phase E adds a +Add attempt with the same secret in url \u2014 that one is BLOCKED so MY MCPS gains only one entry. Ends with the toggle ON.",
  "_phases": [
    "A: open Settings, search 'redaction'; confirm toggle starts OFF",
    "B: click toggle ON; wait for 'Secret visual redaction mode' dropdown (DEMO-PATCH-B fires SECRETS_REGEX recompile)",
    "C: navigate to MCP Servers \u2192 + Add \u2192 paste config with sk- in headers.Authorization \u2192 Save \u2192 expect demo-hdr-bypass-11263 to land in MY MCPS (BUG: should have been blocked)",
    "D: navigate back to MCP Servers \u2192 + Add"
  ],
